my,” while another user said, simply: “Tell the Oscars to SUCK IT.”</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Deserved since it got robbed of the Oscar</p><p> — 優木 せつ菜<img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f1ef-1f1f5.png" alt="🇯🇵" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> | Love Live Superstar S3 SZN (@Nljigakulive) <a href="https://twitter.com/Nljigakulive/status/1886223332376285603?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 3, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> And it somehow is ineligible for the Oscars <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f644.png" alt="🙄" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Well it was the best score of 2024…at least the Grammy&#39;s recognized that</p><p> — Tommy Knox (@tommyknox) <a href="https://twitter.com/tommyknox/status/1886191219748794618?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 2, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Grammys recognizing dune part 2 more than the Academy <a href="https://t.co/idVoq4IGwX">pic.twitter.com/idVoq4IGwX</a></p><p> — agathario lovebot (@shivyhelly) <a href="https://twitter.com/shivyhelly/status/1886195445648801798?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 2, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Tell the Oscars to SUCK IT</p><p> — Le professionale (@lestorynoir_) <a href="https://twitter.com/lestorynoir_/status/1886452978896261293?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 3, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src